  "subject": "Disable 64bit block ciphers",
  "commit_message": "Disable 64bit block ciphers\n\nDisabled SSL 64-bit Block Size Cipher Suites since they are vulnerable to\nthe SWEET32 man-in-the-middle and birthday attacks. Provided a list of\nallowed ciphers in server.xml with proper TLS connector properties. Added\ndefault keystore password.\n\nIssue-ID: POLICY-520\nChange-Id: I9dc4fecddc842e80b433d2709a26e7af1760882a\nSigned-off-by: Temoc Rodriguez <cr056n@att.com>\n",
